# Exam-Killer: Frontend Redesign Blueprint
### Principal Front-End Architect & UI/UX Visionary Report

---

## Executive Summary

This blueprint prescribes a complete front-end redesign of Exam-Killer, an AI-powered study companion targeting Nigerian university students. The redesign must transcend the current utility-first implementation and establish a product that feels as premium and polished as **Vercel**, **Linear**, or **Notion** — deeply intentional, fast, and beautiful.

The guiding philosophy: **"Academic rigor meets digital delight."** Students should feel proud showing this app to their peers.

---

## 1. Design System

### 1.1 Visual Identity

**Aesthetic Direction: Dark-first, Editorial/Premium Tech**

The core aesthetic is inspired by Vercel's deployment dashboard crossed with an editorial intelligence brand. Dark mode is the default (aligned with developer/student culture). The palette is not merely dark — it has *depth, warmth, and hierarchy.*

#### Color Palette

| Token | Value | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `--color-bg-base` | `#080B12` | Main canvas — near-black with deep blue undertone |
| `--color-bg-elevated` | `#0F1420` | Cards, modals, sidebars |
| `--color-bg-surface` | `#171E2E` | Input fields, hover states |
| `--color-border` | `#1E2A40` | Dividers, card borders |
| `--color-border-accent` | `#2D4A7A` | Focus rings, selected states |
| `--color-primary` | `#3D7BF5` | CTAs, active states — electric blue |
| `--color-primary-glow` | `rgba(61,123,245,0.2)` | Glow effects, hover overlays |
| `--color-accent-amber` | `#F5A623` | Scores, streaks, gamification |
| `--color-accent-emerald` | `#22C55E` | Correct answers, success |
| `--color-accent-rose` | `#F43F5E` | Errors, wrong answers, destructive |
| `--color-text-primary` | `#F0F4FF` | Headings, primary body |
| `--color-text-secondary` | `#8896B3` | Labels, captions, helper text |
| `--color-text-muted` | `#4A5568` | Placeholders, disabled states |

**Light mode** will be a tinted warm-white variant, NOT a simple inversion. Light mode is a first-class citizen but secondary to dark.

#### Color Application Logic

- **The 60-30-10 Rule**: 60% background tones, 30% surface/card tones, 10% accent-primary.
- Avoid "rainbow dashboards." Only use accent-amber/emerald/rose for *data-carrying* contexts (scores, feedback).
- No gradients unless intentional: the primary CTA may have a `linear-gradient(135deg, #3D7BF5, #6366F1)` for emphasis.

