## 2. Architectural Strategy

### 2.1 Core Principle: Feature-Sliced Architecture

The current `src/components/{feature}/` structure is correct but incomplete. We will formalize it into **Feature-Sliced Design (FSD)** — a methodology used by Yandex and adopted by large Next.js codebases.

```
src/
├── app/                    # Next.js routing layer (thin pages only)
│   ├── (auth)/             # Auth route group - no layout
│   ├── (app)/              # App route group - with AppShell layout
│   │   ├── dashboard/
│   │   └── workspace/[id]/ # Nested layouts (WorkspaceShell)
│   └── api/                # Server-side API routes
│
├── features/               # Feature modules (primary business logic)
│   ├── workspace/          # Workspace CRUD, WorkspaceCard, WorkspaceCreator
│   ├── flashcards/         # Deck, FlashCard, ReviewQueue, SPRepetitionEngine
│   ├── quizzes/            # QuizBuilder, QuizPlayer, ScoreReveal
│   ├── tutor/              # ChatInterface, MessageBubble, PersonalitySelector
│   ├── analytics/          # StatsCard, ProgressChart, StreakCalendar
│   ├── sources/            # UploadZone, SourceCard, ProcessingStatus
│   └── study-plan/         # PlannerCalendar, ExamCountdown
│
├── widgets/                # Composed UI blocks assembled from features + entities
│   ├── AppShell/           # Global sidebar + topbar layout
│   ├── WorkspaceShell/     # Per-workspace nav + content area
│   └── CommandPalette/     # ⌘K global command palette
│
├── shared/                 # Truly shared, zero business logic
│   ├── ui/                 # Design system primitives (Button, Badge, Card, Input…)
│   ├── hooks/              # useDebounce, useMediaQuery, useLocalStorage
│   ├── lib/                # Firebase clients, OpenAI client, Paystack helpers
│   ├── stores/             # Zustand stores (authStore, workspaceStore, uiStore)
│   └── types/              # Global TypeScript types and Zod schemas
│
└── styles/
    ├── globals.css          # CSS variables (design tokens), base reset
    └── animations.css       # Keyframe definitions
```

**Dependency Rule**: `app → features → widgets → shared`. No layer may import from a layer above it. This is enforced by an ESLint rule.

---

### 2.2 Component Hierarchy

Each `features/{name}/` directory follows a standardized internal structure:

```
features/flashcards/
├── index.ts                # Public API - what this feature exports
├── ui/                     # Presentational components (pure, no Firebase)
│   ├── FlashCard.tsx
│   ├── FlashCardDeck.tsx
│   └── ReviewQueue.tsx
├── model/                  # Business logic: hooks + Zustand slice
│   ├── useFlashcards.ts    # Data fetching hook
│   └── flashcardsStore.ts  # Zustand slice
└── api/                    # API contract: fetch function that calls Next.js route
    └── flashcardsApi.ts
```

This means the Next.js page at `/workspace/[id]/flashcards/page.tsx` only assembles composition, never contains logic.

---

### 2.3 State Management Architecture

**Three-tier state model using Zustand + React Query (TanStack Query):**

| Layer | Tool | Scope | Examples |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Server State** | TanStack Query | Remote data, cached | Workspaces list, flashcards, quiz results |
| **Global Client State** | Zustand | Cross-component, persistent | Auth user, active workspace, sidebar collapse state |
| **Local UI State** | `useState` / `useReducer` | Single component | Modal open, input value, hover state |

**Rules:**
- Never store server data in Zustand. Use TanStack Query's cache as the single source of truth for all Firestore data.
- Zustand is for **ephemeral UI state** (sidebar state, active modal) and session auth.
- `optimistic updates` via `useMutation`'s `onMutate` for instant UI feedback on likes, flips, and ratings.

---

### 2.4 Performance Architecture

| Technique | Application |
|---|---|
| **Route-based code splitting** | Next.js handles this automatically via app router |
| **Lazy loading of heavy features** | Tutor chat, Analytics charts loaded with `next/dynamic` + suspense skeleton |
| **Image optimization** | All images via `next/image` with explicit `width/height` |
| **Font subsetting** | Geist loaded as a CSS variable via `next/font/local` |
| **Web Vitals targets** | LCP < 2.5s, CLS < 0.1, INP < 200ms |
| **Edge caching** | Static workspace metadata served from Vercel Edge Network |
| **Skeleton loading** | All async content has a shimmer skeleton, never raw spinners |
| **Virtualized lists** | Source lists and flashcard decks > 50 items use `@tanstack/virtual` |

