### 2.5 AppShell Layout Design

The global layout is a **three-panel shell** inspired by Linear and VS Code:

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  TopBar: [Logo] [Workspace Switcher]        [⌘K] [👤] │  48px
├────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────┤
│            │                                          │
│  Sidebar   │           Main Content Area              │
│  (260px)   │                                          │
│  ─────     │  Breadcrumb > SubNav > Page Content      │
│  Nav Items │                                          │
│            │                                          │
│  [FREE]    │                                          │
│  Upgrade   │                                          │
│  CTA Card  │                                          │
└────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

- Sidebar collapses to `60px` icon-only mode on screens < `1280px`.
- On mobile (`< 768px`), sidebar becomes a bottom-sheet drawer triggered by a hamburger icon in the TopBar.
- `WorkspaceShell` adds a **secondary horizontal sub-navigation** (Sources, Flashcards, Quizzes, Tutor, Analytics) below the TopBar — a persistent tab bar styled as a pill group.

