## 3. Tech Stack & Tooling

### 3.1 Core Stack (No Changes)

The existing stack is sound. Keep: **Next.js 14 (App Router), TypeScript, Firebase, Tailwind CSS, OpenAI, Pinecone, Paystack.**

### 3.2 New Additions (Justified)

| Library | Purpose | Why Not X? |
|---|---|---|
| `@tanstack/react-query` v5 | Server state management | Replaces custom `useEffect` data fetching; provides caching, retries, optimistic updates |
| `framer-motion` v11 | Complex animation orchestration | CSS-only cannot handle card flip 3D, stagger sequences, or layout animations |
| `zustand` + `immer` | Immutable global state | Already in use; add `immer` middleware for ergonomic nested state mutations |
| `@tanstack/virtual` | List virtualization | Required for sources lists and flashcard decks at scale |
| `zod` | Runtime schema validation | Already in project; expand usage to all API request/response boundaries |
| `lucide-react` | Icon library | Replace any current SVG chaos with a single consistent set |
| `next/font` (Geist) | Self-hosted font optimization | Zero layout shift, optimal loading via CSS variable |
| `recharts` | Analytics charts | Lightweight, composable, works with Tailwind utility classes |
| `cmdk` | Command palette (⌘K) | Powers the global command palette for power-user navigation |
| `@radix-ui/react-*` | Accessible UI primitives | Headless, accessible popovers, dialogs, tooltips — styled via design tokens |

### 3.3 Developer Tooling

| Tool | Config |
|---|---|
| **ESLint** | Add `eslint-plugin-import` with FSD boundary rules to enforce layer dependencies |
| **Prettier** | Already configured; add `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss` for class sorting |
| **TypeScript** | Increase strictness: `noUncheckedIndexedAccess: true`, `exactOptionalPropertyTypes: true` |
| **Storybook** | Set up for the `shared/ui` component library — each primitive documented in isolation |
| **Husky + lint-staged** | Pre-commit hook runs `eslint --fix` and `prettier` before every commit |

