## 4. Agent Implementation Guidelines

When handing this blueprint to execution agents, the following constraints apply:

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Each agent task must map to **exactly one feature directory**. An agent building the `flashcards` feature must only touch `src/features/flashcards/`, `src/app/(app)/workspace/[id]/flashcards/`, and add exports to `src/features/flashcards/index.ts`.

> [!WARNING]
> **Never import from another feature's internal files.** If Feature A needs data from Feature B, it must use Feature B's public `index.ts` export. Violations break the modularity contract.

> [!NOTE]
> All agent deliverables must include:
> - The component file(s)
> - Updated `index.ts` exports
> - A skeleton loading state for any async component
> - A Storybook story (or placeholder) for `shared/ui` primitives

